%N A016631 Decimal expansion of log(8).
%C A016631 log(8) - 2 is the probability that an acute triangle could be formed with the pieces obtained by breaking a stick into three parts at random. The breaking points are chosen with uniform distribution and independently of one another. - _Eugen J. Ionascu_, Feb 19 2011
%C A016631 From _Amiram Eldar_, May 22 2026: (Start)
%C A016631 log(8) - 2 is the probability that when a rod AB is marked at random with points P and Q, and a point R is then taken at random in PQ, then PR^2 + RQ^2 > AP^2 + QB^2 (Wolstenholme, 1871).
%C A016631 log(8) - 2 is the probability that the distances from the sides of a point uniformly selected at random in the interior of an equilateral triangle can be the lengths on an acute triangle (McCall, 1871; Simmons, 1885). (End)
